# Surda Catalog — production environment variables (Railway).
# No secrets here — the app has no API keys. Copy these into Railway → Variables.
# (Values below are the recommended defaults; adjust paths to your Volume mount.)

# Provided automatically by Railway — do NOT set manually.
# PORT=

# --- Persistence (point these INTO the mounted Railway Volume) ---------------
# Create a Volume in Railway and mount it at /data, then:
CATALOG_DB_PATH=/data/catalog.db
UPLOADS_BASE=/data/uploads

# --- Optional tuning (safe defaults already in code) -------------------------
# NODE_ENV=production            # set by the Dockerfile
# LOG_LEVEL=info
# UPLOAD_MAX_BYTES=52428800      # 50 MB max upload
# IMAGE_MAX_CONCURRENCY=2        # bound Sharp memory under concurrent uploads
# FRONTEND_DIST=/app/dist        # default already correct in the image

# --- Do NOT set in single-service mode --------------------------------------
# VITE_API_URL  -> leave UNSET so the frontend uses same-origin relative URLs.
# CORS_ORIGIN   -> not needed (frontend + API share one origin).
